So first of all we need to open our Bash - Ubuntu (Windoes subsystem Linux)

Now activation of the environment ദ്ദി◝ ⩊ ◜.ᐟ

```bash
conda activate qiime2-amplicon-2024.5 
```
Now we will create a file for this project
cd - change directory (navigate to place where you want to create the file)
mnt - mount (we work in Windows but using Linux, this helps to navigate to place where we want to go. It makes the location available inside the Linux file system.)
cd /mnt/c/Users/Kejty
* note: if in your pathway to the desired location are spaces in names e.g. /mnt/c/Users/Kejty laptop! Backword slash (\) needs to be inserted instead of the space with one space after the slash
and the location needs to be wrapped in forwardslashes (/) = /mnt/c/Users/Kejty\ laptop        -to avoid it alsways use underscore _

mkdir - make directory (the file we want to create)
mkdir -p Tutorials        #p stand for parent - we can create more folders at once. Kejty is parent folder if it was missing we could create mkdir -p Kejty/Tutorials - it would create parent folder (Kejty) and inside of the folder, folder Tutorials
